# InvestIQ Dev Workflow

## Always Restart After Changes

**After ANY code change to backend or frontend files, always restart both servers** to ensure the changes take effect. Do not assume hot-reload is sufficient.

### Restart Backend
```powershell
# Kill any running backend
Get-Process python -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force

# Start fresh
Set-Location backend
.\venv\Scripts\uvicorn.exe main:app --reload --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
```

### Restart Frontend
```powershell
# Kill any running frontend (Ctrl+C in the terminal, or:)
Get-Process node -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force

# Start fresh — must use cmd.exe on Windows (npm is a .cmd script, not .exe)
Set-Location "c:\Users\natja\OneDrive\Documents\Nat\Applications\InvestPassiveIncome\frontend"
Start-Process -NoNewWindow -FilePath "cmd.exe" -ArgumentList "/c", "npm run dev"
```

## Known Non-Error: MCP Endpoint in Browser

Opening `http://localhost:8000/mcp` in a browser shows:
```json
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":"server-error","error":{"code":-32600,"message":"Not Acceptable: Client must accept text/event-stream"}}
```
This is **expected and normal**. The `/mcp` endpoint only works with MCP clients (Claude/Cursor), not browsers. To verify the backend is healthy, use `http://127.0.0.1:8000` or `http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs` instead.

## Key URLs

| URL | Purpose |
|---|---|
| http://localhost:5173 | Frontend app |
| http://127.0.0.1:8000 | Backend health check |
| http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs | Swagger API explorer |
| http://127.0.0.1:8000/mcp | MCP only (Claude/Cursor — not browser) |

## Important: Always Use 127.0.0.1 for Backend

Never use `localhost` for the backend on Windows. Node.js 18+ resolves `localhost` to IPv6 `::1`, but Uvicorn binds to IPv4 `127.0.0.1`, causing ECONNREFUSED errors.
